Class EntityAnimation

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • animation.EntityAnimation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class EntityAnimation
extends javafx.scene.Node
    Purpose: EntityAnimation for usage with enemy Entity types. 
     Visual animation, movement, and event-driven progression for enemy Entities.
    Author:
    Hualiang Qin, Louis Galluzzi, Clinton Kral, John Stockey

    • Constructor Detail

      • EntityAnimation

        public EntityAnimation(javafx.scene.layout.StackPane stage,
                       int y,
                       double speed,
                       java.lang.String mode,
                       java.lang.String action,
                       int count,
                       int death,
                       int walk,
                       int attack,
                       TDModel model,
                       int col,
                       Entity zom,
                       int row)
        Purpose: Constructs a new enemy animation based on the passed in parameters.
        Parameters:
        stage - A StackPane for showing the animation.
        y - An int of the row position.
        speed - A double for the speed of the projectile.
        mode - A String of the mode to animate in.
        action - A String of the animation to build and show.
        count - An int of the number of frames for the general animation.
        death - An int of the number of frames for the death animation.
        walk - An int of the number of frames for the walking animation.
        attack - An int of the number of frames for the attacking animation.
        model - A TDModel to call updates on when the animation finishes progressions.
        col - An int of the column the paired Entity exists on.
        zom - An Entity, the paired Entity.
        row - An int of the row the paired Entity exists on.
